author: cbs8
title: Arrest report describes woman found duffel bag slaying
text:
LAS VEGAS (AP) - A police report says a woman arrested in Louisiana described suffocating a 71-year-old Las Vegas neighbor with a trash bag and stuffing her corpse in a duffel bag before her boyfriend hid it in an underground utility vault.
Veronica Houck told Las Vegas police that as they were disposing of Young Suk Sanchez's body, boyfriend Jamar Webb said that if he went to prison, she would too.
Houck and Webb were arrested Oct. 7 in Minden, Louisiana, where they're jailed pending extradition to Nevada to face felony murder, robbery, kidnapping and conspiracy charges.
The Las Vegas police report says Houck and Webb lived at the same extended-stay apartment complex where Houck says they killed Sanchez on Aug. 18.
Sanchez's decomposed body was found by a utility worker Sept. 22.
